just_use verbs.py

# label: EARLY
# role: VERB → PRIMITIVE translator for BFS-solver output

The pipeline is **VERBs → PRIMITIVEs → GESTUREs**. This module
owns the first hop: take a `desc` dict produced by
`bfs_solver._enumerate_moves` and decompose it into a list of
UI primitives suitable for `primitives.send_one`.

Single entry point: `step_to_primitives(desc, board)`.
Internal helpers per verb-type:

- `_extract_absorb` — peel/pluck/yank/steal a card from a
  HELPER stack and merge it onto target. Set extracts may
  need a follow-up merge to reconstitute the legal remnant.
- `_free_pull` — TROUBLE singleton already on board; merge
  onto target.
- `_push` — TROUBLE singleton OR 2-partial onto a HELPER
  stack (the BFS solver merged push and push-merge into one
  desc type).
- `_splice` — split source at k; merge loose into the
  appropriate half per `desc["side"]`.
- `_shift` — peel p_card from donor; split source to isolate
  stolen card; merge p onto source remainder; merge stolen
  onto target.

## Convention: content-based stack lookup

Each primitive's stack indexes are resolved by simulating
splits/merges locally and looking up the next stack by
content tuple-list. This avoids the "appended_after_prev"
symbolic-index bookkeeping the original draft had. As long
as the local board mirrors the server (via
`primitives.apply_locally`), content lookups are stable
across a multi-step trick.

## Convention: split-after semantics

`_plan_split_after(sim, stack_content, k)` translates "the
first `k` cards go to the left half" into the right
`card_index` parameter. The underlying `strategy._apply_split`
uses a leftSplit/rightSplit branch where `left_count = ci+1`
(left) or `ci` (right) depending on which half the click
falls in; the helper hides that asymmetry from callers.

## Convention: pre-flight planning, never post-hoc tidy

Every merge routes through `strategy._plan_merge_stack`
(merge-in-place when legal; otherwise pre-move target into a
hole sized for the EVENTUAL stack). Every interior split
pre-moves the donor into a 4-side-clear region first per
Steve's 2026-04-23 rule. End splits don't pre-move — the
nudge distance stays bounded. There is NO end-of-step tidy
sweep — intermediate frames must stay geometrically clean
all the way through the trick.

## Pointers

- `bfs_solver.claude` — VERB producer. `desc` shape per type
  is documented there + at the source.
- `primitives.claude` — the PRIMITIVE → GESTURE layer.
- `bfs_play.claude` — sole driver today.
- `test_verbs.py` — 7 tests covering all 5 desc types
  (extract_absorb / free_pull / push / splice / shift) with
  hand-built boards.

